A Chinese national is being held at the Kileleshwa Police Station after he was found in possession of five firearms. Dang Pengfei was arrested by a multi-agency team on June 11, 2021 on the Mwingi-Garrissa road at Kanyonyo where he was found in possession of one pistol. A multi-agency team from Kitui led by the County Criminal Investigation Officer (CCIO) Samuel Kobina on Wednesday raided the foreigner’s house at Kaputei Gardens in Kileleshwa where they managed to recover four more firearms and ammunition. According to a police report seen by Citizen Digital, the recovered items are: Further search on the house is still ongoing currently. Also Read: Video Of The Day: CAS Rachel Shebesh and athlete Asbel Kiprop share their mental health journeys